<HEAD weight="bold" >
How should your medicine be kept?
</HEAD>


<BLOCK>
Keep your medicine out of the reach of children.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
Store below 25ºC, protected from light.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
Do not transfer your medicine into another container, as it might get mixed up.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
If you have any Hydrocortone tablets left over when your doctor tells you to stop using them, return them to the pharmacist.
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
Do not use the medicine past the expiry date which is clearly marked on the pack.
</BLOCK>

<CB n=2>

<BLOCK>
REMEMBER, this medicine is for you. Do not share it with anyone else. It may not suit them.
</BLOCK>


